== 1. Junior Salesperson / Sales Analyst

=== Hierarchy Level
Entry-level to 2 years of experience, typically requiring finance or economics degree

=== Key Activities and Responsibilities
- *Client Service*: Supporting senior salespeople with client requests, trade execution, and account management
- *Market Monitoring*: Tracking market developments, economic data, and news flow to inform client conversations
- *Trade Execution Support*: Processing client orders, coordinating with traders, ensuring timely execution
- *Materials Preparation*: Creating pitch materials, market updates, and client presentations
- *CRM Management*: Maintaining client relationship management (CRM) system with interaction logs and opportunities
- *Research Distribution*: Sharing research reports, strategy pieces, and market commentary with clients
- *Administrative Support*: Managing trade confirmations, settlement issues, and client onboarding documentation
- *Learning Products*: Building knowledge of financial instruments, market conventions, and trading mechanics

=== Required Skills

*Technical:*
- Understanding of fixed income, equities, FX, and derivatives markets
- Knowledge of market microstructure and execution mechanics
- Bloomberg terminal proficiency (trading systems, market data, client communication)
- Excel skills for basic analysis and client materials
- Familiarity with order management systems and execution platforms
- Understanding of regulatory requirements (best execution, suitability, disclosure)

*Interpersonal:*
- Strong communication skills (verbal and written)
- Active listening and understanding client needs
- Relationship building and networking ability
- Professional presence and confidence
- Team collaboration (working with traders, research, other salespeople)
- Time management (juggling multiple clients and requests)
- Resilience and handling rejection (not every pitch succeeds)

*Regulatory:*
- Understanding of client classification (retail, professional, eligible counterparty)
- Knowledge of best execution obligations
- Awareness of suitability and appropriateness requirements
- Familiarity with market conduct rules and insider trading restrictions
- Understanding of conflicts of interest and disclosure obligations

