=== Revenue Models and Economics

*Commission-Based (Traditional):*
- Equities: 3-10 basis points (bps) on notional traded
- Fixed income: 1-5bp on notional
- FX: 0.5-3bp on notional
- Derivatives: Varies widely (options 3-15bp, futures 0.5-2bp, swaps 1-5bp)

*Spread-Based (Market Making):*
- Bank buys from client at bid, sells at offer, captures spread
- FX: 0.5-5 pip spread depending on currency pair and size
- Fixed income: 2-10bp spread on corporate bonds
- OTC derivatives: 1-5% of option premium or swap value

*Structured Product Fees:*
- Upfront fees: 0.5-2% of notional on structured notes
- Ongoing fees: 0.1-0.5% pa on principal-protected products
- Structuring fees: 0.25-1% on complex bespoke solutions

