=== MiFID II Impact on Sales

*Background:*
MiFID II (Markets in Financial Instruments Directive II), effective January 2018 in Europe, unbundled research from execution. While Australian banks aren't directly regulated by MiFID II, many have global clients subject to it.

*Key Changes:*
- *Research Unbundling*: European asset managers must pay for research separately from execution (can't bundle)
- *Best Execution*: Enhanced requirements to demonstrate best execution achieved
- *Inducements*: Restrictions on gifts, entertainment, and benefits to clients
- *Transparency*: Enhanced reporting on execution quality and costs

*Adaptation Strategies:*
- *Value-Added Services*: Focus on unique insights (market color, flow intelligence, access to traders)
- *Execution Quality*: Invest in algos, smart order routing, best execution frameworks
- *Customization*: Tailor research and ideas to specific client needs (not generic research)
- *Technology*: Provide data, analytics, and tools beyond basic execution
- *Relationship Depth*: Deepen advisory relationships (portfolio construction, risk management consulting)

